<div id="review_2301158416" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2301158416" />
    <a title="Fiona MacDonald" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2417021-fiona-macdonald"><img alt="Fiona MacDonald" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624045599p2/2417021.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2301158416?book_show_action=true">Jul 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fiona MacDonald" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fiona MacDonald" href="/user/show/2417021-fiona-macdonald">Fiona MacDonald</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780525434139" href="/book/show/34626038-house-of-the-sleeping-beauties-and-other-stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2417021-fiona-macdonald?shelf=books-that-have-been-recommended">books-that-have-been-recommended</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2417021-fiona-macdonald?shelf=my-books">my-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2417021-fiona-macdonald?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2301158416" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10381544183761688316">An absolutely bizarre reading experience. &apos;House of the Sleeping Beauties&apos; is divided into three stories. The title story (and the longest) sees an old man going to a mysterious house and paying to sleep next to an unconscious woman of his choice. He does this numerous times, each time with a different woman. The women have all been drugged, and if he wants to, he can do anything he wants to the woman because she will be unconscious. But apparently this isn&apos;t rape, because in choosing to take th</span>
  <span id="freeText10381544183761688316" style="display:none">An absolutely bizarre reading experience. 'House of the Sleeping Beauties' is divided into three stories. The title story (and the longest) sees an old man going to a mysterious house and paying to sleep next to an unconscious woman of his choice. He does this numerous times, each time with a different woman. The women have all been drugged, and if he wants to, he can do anything he wants to the woman because she will be unconscious. But apparently this isn't rape, because in choosing to take the drugged tablets, the woman are consenting... besides, this actually turns out to be the thing furthest from his mind, as he chooses to simply smell the woman and touch her teeth etc which in turn brings up memories of his childhood and past relationships. I found this whole story extremely uncomfortable despite the fact I'm sure the author is trying to create a narrative that doesn't come off as simply perverted. The writing itself was lyrical and elegant, but I couldn't come to terms with what was actually going on in this weird house and how 'normal' everything was being portrayed. The other 2 stories were equally bizarre - one about a woman removing her arm to give to a man so he can carry it around with him, and the other about a man who recalls the various puppies and birds that have died in his care over the years...</span>
  <a data-text-id="10381544183761688316" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


