<span id="freeTextContainer5323506199605542969">Hmm, mixed feelings... 3.5 stars<br/>Two of the stories had that &quot;Japanese weirdness&quot; that I like. But both stories had a non-end. The first one was by far the best. If it was just that, I would give 4 stars.<br/>The second story started interesting, but I would like a meaning in the end. I didn&apos;t get anything.<br/>The third... It was a story about a man that doesn&apos;t like people and he has many birds. I felt like the translation ruined this story for me, it was a little bit confusing.<br/><br/>In any case, I think the w</span>
  <span id="freeText5323506199605542969" style="display:none">Hmm, mixed feelings... 3.5 stars<br />Two of the stories had that "Japanese weirdness" that I like. But both stories had a non-end. The first one was by far the best. If it was just that, I would give 4 stars.<br />The second story started interesting, but I would like a meaning in the end. I didn't get anything.<br />The third... It was a story about a man that doesn't like people and he has many birds. I felt like the translation ruined this story for me, it was a little bit confusing.<br /><br />In any case, I think the writer is a very good one.</span>
