<div id="review_2153784624" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2153784624" />
    <a title="Mizuki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16842102-mizuki"><img alt="Mizuki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1368277474p2/16842102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2153784624?book_show_action=true">Oct 15, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mizuki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mizuki" href="/user/show/16842102-mizuki">Mizuki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789863592600" href="/book/show/31753033">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16842102-mizuki?shelf=chinese-translation">chinese-translation</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16842102-mizuki?shelf=pretty-good">pretty-good</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16842102-mizuki?shelf=japanese-authors">japanese-authors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2153784624" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1642503522599196509">My review for <i>The Old Capital</i> by the same author: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1905382755?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1'>https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a><br/><br/><i>Sleeping Beauties</i> or <i>House of the Sleeping Beauties</i> by Yasunari Kawabata is not a pleasant book to read.<br/><br/>The story itself is simple enough, with only a handful of characters occupied the story: An old man was invited to a very private inn to spend a night with the &apos;sleeping beauties&apos;: young beautiful naked girls who had been drugged into heavy sleep. Old men were allowed to spend nights sleeping beside these</span>
  <span id="freeText1642503522599196509" style="display:none">My review for <i>The Old Capital</i> by the same author: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1905382755?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1">https://www.goodreads.com/review/show...</a><br><br><i>Sleeping Beauties</i> or <i>House of the Sleeping Beauties</i> by Yasunari Kawabata is not a pleasant book to read.<br><br>The story itself is simple enough, with only a handful of characters occupied the story: An old man was invited to a very private inn to spend a night with the 'sleeping beauties': young beautiful naked girls who had been drugged into heavy sleep. Old men were allowed to spend nights sleeping beside these girls in separate scarlet chambers within the inn, but sexual intercourse with the girls is entirely forbidden. <br><br>The old man at first only visited the inn out of pure curiosity, but after he tried this special experience once, soon he found himself coming back for more. His different nights with different 'sleeping beauties' provoked different memories from various parts of his life, reminding him with the different women he had had in the past, provoking different regret and sense of guilt. <br><br>Like the readers, the old man found himself trapped in this heavenly/nightmarish realm of fantasy and he had difficulty tearing himself out (he even had fits of anger for a few times because he felt mocked by the girls' beauty and he had thought of violating the girls against the rules as a revenge for his lost youth and strength), in the end, something dramatic happened, breaking the spell.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1508076449i/24180587._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Alright, the idea of old men spending nights beside drugged naked girls and were allowed to play with their bodies is both resentful and spellbinding at the same time. Damn! That sounds just like some sick fantasy of some dirty old man! <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1508076449i/24180586._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>(Link: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://view.inews.qq.com/a/HNN2016042401188900">http://view.inews.qq.com/a/HNN2016042...</a>)<br><br>However, I appreciate Mr. Kawabata for his boldness in exploring forbidden areas, his skillful writing and slow burnt story telling also helps to craft this fascinating private realm of sinful beauty, secret desires, longing and regret; a realm which is both highly erotic and innocent at the same time. It is an extremely well crafted case study of how an old man dealt with old age (and the shame it brings), his loss of sexual strength, fear of death, longing for youth and beauty, and the regret from his past. <br><br>Unsurprisingly, Mr. Kawabata wrote this novella during the twilight years of his life.<br><br>Of course the treatment of women in this story is pretty much problematic. The young, beautiful girls in the story are all drugged and played with like playthings with zero will of their own, and the only active female character in the story: the middle age innkeeper, is described as physically unattractive and mean. Still, I cannot help from enjoying the fetish and necrophilic undertone of the old man's activities with his sleeping beauties.<br><br>At one side there is the youth and beauty represented by the helpless sleeping girls slumbering inside a scarlet chamber, on the other side, we have an old man, bearing the weight of the approaching death and the shame of old age, laying beside the girls. When beauty and death come so close and intimate with one another, things become sickening and intriguing, purifying and fatal at the very same time.<br><br>It is not a book for everyone, but if you wanted a taste of twisted, forbidden desire, you can very well try!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1642503522599196509" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


