<span id="freeTextContainer7453759587081555916"><a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[<br/>Attention! This part contains spoilers for <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14032.House_of_the_Sleeping_Beauties_and_Other_Stories' title='House of the Sleeping Beauties and Other Stories by Yasunari Kawabata' rel='nofollow noopener'>House of the Sleeping Beauties and Other Stories</a> and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5947099.Memories_of_My_Melancholy_Whores' title='Memories of My Melancholy Whores by Gabriel García Márquez' rel='nofollow noopener'>Memories of My Melancholy Whores</a>.<br/><br/><b><u>Manuel for writing a successful book about brothels.</u><br/>Take an old man<br/>Take a virgin whore or better - several;<br/>Put them together in the same room, to have a desirable outcome - for several nights. The desired outcome here is of course to hook the reader;<br/>The girl must be sleeping the whole time;<br/>The man must sit or lie down and admire her innocence and her bea</b></span></span>
  <span id="freeText7453759587081555916" style="display:none"><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[<br />Attention! This part contains spoilers for <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14032.House_of_the_Sleeping_Beauties_and_Other_Stories" title="House of the Sleeping Beauties and Other Stories by Yasunari Kawabata" rel="nofollow noopener">House of the Sleeping Beauties and Other Stories</a> and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5947099.Memories_of_My_Melancholy_Whores" title="Memories of My Melancholy Whores by Gabriel García Márquez" rel="nofollow noopener">Memories of My Melancholy Whores</a>.<br /><br /><b><u>Manuel for writing a successful book about brothels.</u><br />Take an old man<br />Take a virgin whore or better - several;<br />Put them together in the same room, to have a desirable outcome - for several nights. The desired outcome here is of course to hook the reader;<br />The girl must be sleeping the whole time;<br />The man must sit or lie down and admire her innocence and her beauty;<br />The man must remember his past;<br />Nothing happens between them;<br />The end! </b><br /><br />Maybe you'll get a Nobel Prize - they both did. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />Ok. Now the serious part. This was an absolute "esoteric masterpiece" as Mishima describes, with unbelievable openness, passion, and reality - Japanese surrealism mixed up with Marquez-esque magical realism. Kawabata's writing is magic. No matter how absurd the plot is, you are hooked.</span>
